Package edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre

Class Number

java.lang.Object
edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre.Number
All Implemented Interfaces:
Expression, Logical, Numeric, Parameter, Simplifiable, Typed, Value, Serializable, Comparable<Logical>
public class Number extends Object implements Numeric, Value
Represents numbers (using the Java double data type) as values. Number objects are singletons, meaning there can only ever be one number object with a given value. This allows numbers to be compared using ==.
Author:
Stephen G. Ware

    • get

      public static final Number get(Number value)
      Converts a Java Number to a value, interning it to ensure that there is only ever one number object with this value. If this method is called multiple times with the same input value, it will return the same number object every time.

      Returns:
